This paper is primarily focused on visual object tracking, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a new deep learning architecture for one-shot learning, which involves training a model to recognize new objects from just one example. This is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves real-time processing of video data, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) categories.
